Dignitaries were thrilled on Wednesday by a special parade organised by the members of Nigeria’s Armed Forces at the Eagle Square, Abuja, venue of the Democracy Day celebration. Members of the Armed Forces including the Army, Navy, Air Force and Police are thrilling the dignitaries in parade march, in slow and quick time. The parade march was being done after President Muhammadu Buhari inspected guards of parade and acknowledged cheers from invited guests. Armed Forces tasked to deepen democracy - former CDS Armed Forces Remembrance Day: VP, WWII veteran, lay wreaths at Abuja cenotaph Armed Forces Remembrance Day: Soldier’s insurance scheme increases death benefit-Ihejirika Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin